<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880511-0039 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: General Instrument Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> GRL </CO><IN> TEL </IN><TEXT>   General Instrument Corp. said it received an order for electronic systems for satellite television that could be valued at as much as $100 million.    The order calls for first delivery of the systems to British Satellite Broadcasting Ltd. in June 1989.    General Instrument, a New York-based maker of electronic communications equipment, said it also entered into a joint venture with British Satellite to market and distribute various electronic products for a direct broadcast satellite system in Britain.    British Satellite has the exclusive franchise for high-powered direct broadcast satellite service in Britain to begin in September 1989. </TEXT></DOC>